                            <comment id="18796" author="springboy" created="Wed, 26 Jul 2006 19:04:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Corby&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Shame on us for not providing any tests; I will certainly castigate whoever the original writer of @Configurable was.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll add test coverage and fix whatever bugs are present in the current build.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cheers&lt;br/&gt;
Rick&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="18892" author="corby" created="Thu, 3 Aug 2006 02:23:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, Rick. Is this going to be scheduled for 2.0 RC3? We need these test cases to get @Configurable working before 2.0 Final.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="18894" author="springboy" created="Thu, 3 Aug 2006 02:29:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Corby&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll address this tomorrow. It&apos;s my second to last Spring issue to resolve before Spring 2.0 final &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cheers&lt;br/&gt;
Rick&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="18900" author="springboy" created="Fri, 4 Aug 2006 01:27:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Corby&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Spring codebase does have some text cases for the @Configurable supprt; they are not comprehensive, as they exercise only the sunny day paths and not those scenarios where things go belly up.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This test fixture is called BeanConfigurerTests and it exists in the tiger/tests directory of the Spring CVS HEAD.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What exactly is broken in the current implementation? I can certainly bang out some tests cases for the rainy day paths (and I&apos;m going to do just that prior to leaving the office for the weekend), but having a little more to go on would be good. I know there is an existing issue with regard to multiple contexts, because the AnnotationBeanConfigurerAspect is a singleton aspect, but that is a known &apos;feature&apos; that will (so far as I know) not be being addressed in the 2.0 timeframe (don&apos;t quote me on that though). I&apos;ll email Adrian (Colyer) now about that actually.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cheers&lt;br/&gt;
Rick&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="18925" author="corby" created="Sun, 6 Aug 2006 09:17:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, Rick. This issue is fixed from my perspective. I can successfully run BeanConfigurerTests, and I can use this as a basis point to diagnose problems I am having with @Configurable and Hibernate.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
